SIMPLE: superfluous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Superfluous
<hw>Su*per"flu*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>superfluus</ets> overflowing; <ets>super</ets> over, above +
<ets>fluere</ets> to flow. See <er>Super-</er>, and
<er>Fluent</er>.]</ety> <def>More than is wanted or is sufficient;
rendered unnecessary by superabundance; unnecessary; useless; excessive;
<as>as, a <ex>superfluous</ex> price</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An authority which makes all further argument or illustration
<qex>superfluous</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>E. Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Superfluous interval</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>an
interval that exceeds a major or perfect interval by a
semitone.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unnecessary; useless; exuberant; excessive;
redundant; needless.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Su*per"flu*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Su*per"flu*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superflux</ent>⟦br⟧
